    "caption": "Four stomachs, eight hours of chewing, and still totally calm.",
    "shortDescription": "Cows have four stomach compartments that work like a slow, efficient recycling plant for grass. They swallow a mouthful, let it soften in the first stomach, then bring it back up to chew it again — a process called chewing the cud. Cows have best friends in their herd and get stressed when separated from them. Fun fact: Cows can sleep standing up but only dream when they lie down."
